BRACE EXPANSION
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Brace expansion is a mechanism by which arbitrary strings may be generated, for commands that will take multiple arguements.
 -  For the below examples, the first example is equivalent to the second command:
 
 
 	$ mkdir /var/log/{auth,syslog,dmesg}_log
	$ mkdir /var/log/auth_log /var/log/syslog_log /var/log/dmesg_log
	
	
	
mkdir /absolute/path/{stuff_to_iterate}<common>
mkdir /absolute/path/<common>{iterate1,iterate2,iterate3}


==================================================================================================================================================



#---------[	1.1	]--------#


mkdir $HOME/11{23,34,45,56}


===================================================================================================================================================


#--------------[	1.2	]-------------#



touch {1..5}.txt {6..9}~.txt


====================================================================================================================================================

#--------------[	1.3	]--------------#



ls -1 $HOME/1123/[^~].txt



-1 indicates vertical sorting of ls command, [^~] indicates to exclude if starting with a '~' character. 	'^' indicates a logical NOT in regex





===============================================================================================================================================================


	






